<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="333" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[118,769,983,1342]" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis box="[163,426,1254,1278]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[459,691,1254,1278]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellipsoidea">
<emphasis box="[459,691,1254,1278]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Benstonea ellipsoidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confined to the mountain rainforests of the island of 
<collectingRegion box="[643,739,1286,1310]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[118,222,1318,1342]" name="Indonesia" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" box="[237,375,1318,1342]" firstAuthor="STONE" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1978">STONE, 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="333" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[118,771,1358,1766]" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis box="[163,331,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Observations. –</emphasis>
This taxon was described on the basis of an immature infructescence 
<emphasis box="[411,586,1390,1414]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">(Warburg16151)</emphasis>
, which is almost impossible to distinguish from 
<emphasis box="[444,569,1422,1446]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Beccari s.n.</emphasis>
, 
<typeStatus box="[582,627,1422,1446]" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dipsaceus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Pandanus dipsaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In his revision, 
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" box="[396,539,1454,1478]" firstAuthor="STONE" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1978">STONE (1978)</bibRefCitation>
maintained these two as separate species, albeit with much doubt. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellipsoidea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Benstonea ellipsoidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is indeed very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[459,556,1518,1542]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[459,556,1518,1542]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">B. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs in the shape and dimensions of itsdrupes and the syncarps. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName box="[118,258,1582,1606]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellipsoidea">
<emphasis box="[118,258,1582,1606]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">B.ellipsoidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found at high altitude on limestone substrate in Sulawesi (KEIM, pers. comm.), whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[577,674,1614,1638]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis box="[577,674,1614,1638]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">B. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in lowland peat swamp forests from 
<collectingCountry box="[518,612,1646,1670]" name="Vietnam" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
to Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[118,221,1678,1702]" name="Malaysia" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, Borneo and 
<collectingCountry box="[366,472,1678,1702]" name="Indonesia" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(Bangka, 
<collectingRegion box="[587,683,1678,1702]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="10" pageNumber="333">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
). Given the strong ecological differences between these taxa, we tentatively follow the treatment of 
<bibRefCitation author="STONE" box="[455,604,1742,1766]" firstAuthor="STONE" pageId="10" pageNumber="333" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1978">STONE (1978)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
